{
  "style": "IEEE",
  "texts": [
    "The standard parametrization is also used for the PMNS matrix U PMNS =  -iδ PMNS -x 12 k 23 -k 12 x 23 x 13 e iδ PMNS k 12 k 23 -x 12 x 23 x 13 e iδ PMNS x 23 k 13 x 12 x 23 -k 12 k 23 x 13 e iδ PMNS -x 23 k 12 -x 12 k 23 x 13 e iδ PMNS k 23, (C.3) where x ij = sin θ ij and k ij = cos θ ij.",
    "A global fit of the parameters in (C.3) gives values which depend on the assumed hierarchy among the neutrino masses [103]: for normal ordering sin 2 θ 12 = 0.308 +0.012 -0.011, sin 2 θ 23 = 0.470 +0.017 -0.013, sin 2 θ 13 = 0.02215 +0.00056 -0.00058, δ PMNS = (212 +26 -41) •, (C.4) for inverted ordering sin 2 θ 12 = 0.308 +0.012 -0.011, sin 2 θ 23 = 0.550 +0.012 -0.015, sin 2 θ 13 = 0.02231 +0.00056 -0.00056, δ PMNS = (274 +22 -25) •.",
    "(C.5) A complete discussion is in[2].",
    "For |V cb | a solution based on µ -e universality violation has been proposed in[6].",
    "Recent analyses of lepton flavour violating b → s modes are in[19][20][21][22][23][24][25]."
  ],
